                        <b>Objective:</b>
                        <br>
                        To test that additions to Intangible assets are correctly valued, correctly classified  and are in the name of the company.
                        <br><br>
                        <b>Audit Approach:</b>
                        <br>
                        Select material acquisitions and:
                        <br>
                        (a) Agree to supporting documentation;
                        <br>
                        (b) Ensure that no expense items (e.g. research costs) have been capitalised as an asset;
                        <br>
                        (c) Confirm that the acquisition was properly authorised;
                        <br>
                        (d) Follow through to the entry in the asset register;
                        <br>
                        (e) Ensure the initial cost includes the purchase price, including import duties and non-refundable purchase taxes; as well as any directly attributable cost of preparing the asset for its intended use (SME18.10);
                        <br>
                        (f) Ensure that no borrowing costs are capitalised as part of the cost of the intangible assets;
                        <br>
                        (g) Ensure that assets are only recognised if it meets the recognition criteria in the International Financial Reporting Standard for Small and Medium-sized Entities, i.e. it must be identifiable (separable or arising from contractual or other legal rights), future economic benefits must be probable, its value can be reliably measured and it was not internally generated (SME18.2 and 18.4).
